All the tankers function as "thermoses" that can preserve the freight temperature even under freezing temperatures of the environment (heat losses reach no more than 2-3 &ordm;C per diem). There are truck tankers for the transportation of special chemical freights of high temperature (up to 80 &ordm;C), with freight heating provided during transportation. Truck tankers allow for the transportation of freight under pressure.<br /><br />

